cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the use of bibliometric data, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on citation impact and the analysis of publications suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely categories. The mention of problems in percentile calculation and rank assignment may also relate to cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CR (Computational Complexity and Cryptography). Finally, the use of percentiles in analyzing data could also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
